lling them to a vendor to clear space.<br><br>I'm also I a Wood Elf so I can craft Imbued weapons for those who worship Tunare or Karana. Any other Fier`Dal smiths out there? What kind of demand have you seen? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubladeofevil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blade of Evil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Perpetually Pissed</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/22/02 1:50:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://thevornskr.homestead.com/files/velveportrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fine Steel Plate, what should I charge?</span><hr size=1> Whatever you and your buyer feel is fair.<br><br>Neither formula you've stated is overly efficient because (like banded) the molds vary in price that is not relative to the finished product's worth in armor.<br><br>I try to sell at a price that covers expenses right now, not for profit.  I'll worry about profit the day I become grandmaster and some of this stuff is trivial to me.  Since I still skill from it all, I figure I get a free practice session, and a few extra plat in the pocket if I don't scew it up.<br><br>But that's what I do. <p><B><font color="darkred">Velve D'Verin</font><Br><small>51st Reaver of Innoruuk</small><br>Kyorl'jabbuk of<BR><a href="http://members.tripod.com/selquar">House Sel'Quar</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utrinnityfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trinnity FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/22/02 2:36:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fine Steel Plate, what should I charge?</span><hr size=1> You have to be patient, particularly on a small server like FV.  Post here that you are offering those services and what your prices are and wait...It may not be today or even a week from today, but keep at it and you will be known...charge fair prices and they will come...<br><br>A review of EQtraders.com shows that the standard rate for almost all servers is 75pp/folded sheet.  I don't know of anyone who uses pp/AC but that doesn't mean you couldn't charge that way.<br><br>Good luck! <p>Trinnity X'Vex <BR>Shadowknight <BR>Indigo Void <BR>Firiona Vie <BR><BR>"For Hate's sake, I spit at thee..."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lawrennds>LawrennDS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/25/02 11:52:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fine Steel Plate, what should I charge?</span><hr size=1> The last time I played a warrior character, I went to a master smith who understood money troubles and was charging about 250pp per two items (bought arms, legs, helmet and bracers from him- two occasions) of any color I wanted... seemed reasonable. Part of the deal we had was that I sent him more customers, and I did.<br><br>I think blacksmithing is a great skill, but in the beginning you'll get screwed a lot just be even TRYING to make something. I hear the above suggested rate as pretty much standard, more often than not. (75pp per sheet, 10pp per AC) All it takes is one good customer to spread the word, so maybe cutting a good deal is a good pump primer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showPrevMessage?topicID=176.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showNextMessage?topicID=176.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=176.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.threadControl?topicID=176.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=176.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=176.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OOC Forum<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox<option value="firionaviefrm10">A Bard for a Day<option value="firionaviefrm23">Hero Heart Tavern<option value="firionaviefrm15">The Polling Booth<option value="firionaviefrm40">Kudos!<option value="firionaviefrm2">The Market Square<option value="firionaviefrm22">The Tradeskill Shop<option value="firionav